<rml>
<head>
	<link type="text/rcss" href="/../Tests/Data/style.rcss"/>
	<title>CSS Flexbox Test: gap - rows and columns</title>
	<link href="https://test.csswg.org/suites/css-align-3_dev/nightly-unstable/xhtml1/reference/gap-003-ltr-ref.xht"
		  rel="source"/>
	<link href="mailto:argyle@google.com" rel="author" title="Adam Argyle"/>
	<style>
		section {
			background-color: green;
			height: 200px;
			width: 400px;
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}

		section > div {
			background-color: grey;
			width: 190px;
		}

		section > div:nth-child(1),
		section > div:nth-child(3) {
			margin-right: 20px;
		}

		section > div:nth-child(3),
		section > div:nth-child(4) {
			margin-top: 20px;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
<p>Test passes if there are <strong> green lines between boxes</strong>.</p>
<section>
	<div></div>
	<div></div>
	<div></div>
	<div></div>
</section>
</body>
</rml>
